{"title":"随机事件的独立性","uid":"8eccb33eadcfc07f260da794eb4df1d5","slug":"随机事件的独立性","date":"2023-09-12T00:41:58.000Z","updated":"2023-09-16T02:56:07.890Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/随机事件的独立性.json","keywords":null,"cover":null,"content":"<h2 id=\"事件的独立性\"><a href=\"#事件的独立性\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"事件的独立性\"></a>事件的独立性</h2><span id=\"more\"></span>\n<p>$P(B \\mid A)=P(B\\mid \\bar A)$，则A与B相互独立。（充要条件）</p>\n<p>设A，B是试验E的两个事件,若满足</p>\n<script type=\"math/tex; mode=display\">\nP(AB)=P(A)P(B)</script><p>则事件A与B相互独立。</p>\n<p>上述两个公式是等价的，第一个式子常用来判断事件的独立性，而第二个式子常用来计算概率。当然也可以将式子转化为第二个式子来证明事件相互独立。若A与B相互独立，则他们的对立事件也相互独立，即$A,\\bar B$等也相互独立。</p>\n<p>定义 设$  A_{1}, A_{2}, \\ldots, A_{n}  $为试验$  E  $的事件， 若对任意的$  s(1&lt;s \\leq n)  $及$  1 \\leq i_{1}&lt;i_{2}&lt;\\ldots&lt;i_{s} \\leq   n $, 有</p>\n<script type=\"math/tex; mode=display\">\nP\\left(A i_{1} A i_{2} \\ldots A i_{s}\\right)=P\\left(A i_{1}\\right) P\\left(A i_{2}\\right) \\ldots P\\left(A i_{s}\\right)</script><p>成立，则称事件$  A_{1}, A_{2}, \\ldots, A_{n}  $相互独立.</p>\n<p>若对一切$  1 \\leq i_{1}&lt;i_{2} \\leq n $, 有</p>\n<script type=\"math/tex; mode=display\">\nP\\left(A i_{1} A i_{2}\\right)=P\\left(A i_{1}\\right) P\\left(A i_{2}\\right)</script><p>成立，则称事件$  A_{1}, A_{2}, \\ldots, A_{n}  $两两独立。</p>\n<blockquote><span class=\"custom-blockquote-svg\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" data-reactroot=\"\">\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M22 12C22 6.5 17.5 2 12 2C6.5 2 2 6.5 2 12C2 17.5 6.5 22 12 22C13.8 22 15.5 21.5 17 20.6L22 22L20.7 17C21.5 15.5 22 13.8 22 12Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M15.97 11.5H16.04C17.12 11.5 18 12.38 18 13.47V13.53C18 14.62 17.12 15.5 16.03 15.5H15.96C14.88 15.5 14 14.62 14 13.53V13.46C14 12.38 14.88 11.5 15.97 11.5Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M7.97 11.5H8.04C9.12 11.5 10 12.38 10 13.47V13.53C10 14.62 9.12 15.5 8.03 15.5H7.97C6.88 15.5 6 14.62 6 13.53V13.46C6 12.38 6.88 11.5 7.97 11.5Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M17 8.5C15.23 8.97 14.07 10.84 14.01 13.27C14 13.33 14 13.4 14 13.47V13.5\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M9 8.5C7.23 8.97 6.07 10.84 6.01 13.27C6 13.33 6 13.4 6 13.47V13.5\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M15.97 11.5H16.04C17.12 11.5 18 12.38 18 13.47V13.53C18 14.62 17.12 15.5 16.03 15.5H15.96C14.88 15.5 14 14.62 14 13.53V13.46C14 12.38 14.88 11.5 15.97 11.5Z\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M7.97 11.5H8.04C9.12 11.5 10 12.38 10 13.47V13.53C10 14.62 9.12 15.5 8.03 15.5H7.97C6.88 15.5 6 14.62 6 13.53V13.46C6 12.38 6.88 11.5 7.97 11.5Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><p>n个事件相互独立比两两独立更强的结论。</p></blockquote>\n<p>定理：若n个事件$  A_{1} ， A_{2} ， \\ldots, A_{n}  $相互独立， 则将$  A_{1} ， A_{2} ， \\ldots, A_{n}  $中的任意多个事件换成它 们的对立事件后，所得到的个事件仍然相互独立。</p>\n<blockquote><span class=\"custom-blockquote-svg\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" data-reactroot=\"\">\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M22 12C22 6.5 17.5 2 12 2C6.5 2 2 6.5 2 12C2 17.5 6.5 22 12 22C13.8 22 15.5 21.5 17 20.6L22 22L20.7 17C21.5 15.5 22 13.8 22 12Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M15.97 11.5H16.04C17.12 11.5 18 12.38 18 13.47V13.53C18 14.62 17.12 15.5 16.03 15.5H15.96C14.88 15.5 14 14.62 14 13.53V13.46C14 12.38 14.88 11.5 15.97 11.5Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path fill=\"\" d=\"M7.97 11.5H8.04C9.12 11.5 10 12.38 10 13.47V13.53C10 14.62 9.12 15.5 8.03 15.5H7.97C6.88 15.5 6 14.62 6 13.53V13.46C6 12.38 6.88 11.5 7.97 11.5Z\" undefined=\"1\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M17 8.5C15.23 8.97 14.07 10.84 14.01 13.27C14 13.33 14 13.4 14 13.47V13.5\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M9 8.5C7.23 8.97 6.07 10.84 6.01 13.27C6 13.33 6 13.4 6 13.47V13.5\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M15.97 11.5H16.04C17.12 11.5 18 12.38 18 13.47V13.53C18 14.62 17.12 15.5 16.03 15.5H15.96C14.88 15.5 14 14.62 14 13.53V13.46C14 12.38 14.88 11.5 15.97 11.5Z\"></path>\n<path stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke=\"\" d=\"M7.97 11.5H8.04C9.12 11.5 10 12.38 10 13.47V13.53C10 14.62 9.12 15.5 8.03 15.5H7.97C6.88 15.5 6 14.62 6 13.53V13.46C6 12.38 6.88 11.5 7.97 11.5Z\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><p>若  n  个事件$ A_{1}, A_{2} ， \\ldots, A_{n}  $相互独立，将这  n  个事件任意分成  k  组，同一个事件不能同时属于 两个不同的组，则对每组的事件进行求和、积、差、 对立等运算所得到的 k 个事件也相互独立.<br>特别地，若  A ， B ， C  为三个相互独立的事件，则其中 任意两个事件的和、差、交及其逆与另一个事件 或其逆都是相互独立的。</p></blockquote>\n<p>考虑$  A_{1}, A_{2}, \\ldots, A_{n} $至少有一个发生 的概率，其中  $0&lt;P\\left(A_{i}\\right)=p_{i}&lt;1 $，则：</p>\n<p>(1) 若$  A_{1}, A_{2}, \\ldots, A_{n}  $互不相容，由概率 的有限可加性可得</p>\n<p>$p=P\\left(A_{1}\\right)+P\\left(A_{2}\\right)+\\ldots+P\\left(A_{n}\\right)=p_{1}+p_{2}+\\ldots+p_{n}$</p>\n<p>(2) 若$  A_{1}, A_{2}, \\ldots, A_{n}  $相互独立，由对偶原理可得</p>\n<script type=\"math/tex; mode=display\">\n\n\\begin{aligned}\np & =P\\left(A_{1} \\cup A_{2} \\cup \\cdots \\cup A_{n}\\right) \\\\\n& =1-P\\left(\\bar{A}_{1} \\bar{A}_{2} \\cdots \\bar{A}_{n}\\right) \\\\\n& =1-P\\left(\\bar{A}_{1}\\right) P\\left(\\bar{A}_{2}\\right) \\cdots P\\left(\\bar{A}_{n}\\right)\n\\end{aligned}</script><p>特别，当$  P\\left(A_{i}\\right)=p, i=1,2, \\ldots, n $, 有</p>\n<script type=\"math/tex; mode=display\">\n\\begin{array}{l}\n\\left.P\\left(A_{1} \\cup A_{2} \\cup \\ldots \\cup A_{n}\\right\\}\\right)=1-(1-p)^{n} \\\\\nP\\left\\{A_{1} \\cup A_{2} \\cup \\cdots \\cup A_{n}\\right\\}=\\lim _{n \\rightarrow \\infty}\\left[1-(1-p)^{n}\\right]=1\n\\end{array}</script>","text":"事件的独立性 $P(B \\mid A)=P(B\\mid \\bar A)$，则A与B相互独立。（充要条件） 设A，B是试验E的两个事件,若满足 P(AB)=P(A...","permalink":"/post/随机事件的独立性","photos":[],"count_time":{"symbolsCount":"1.8k","symbolsTime":"2 mins."},"categories":[{"name":"概率论与数理统计","slug":"概率论与数理统计","count":4,"path":"api/categories/概率论与数理统计.json"}],"tags":[],"toc":"<ol class=\"toc\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#%E4%BA%8B%E4%BB%B6%E7%9A%84%E7%8B%AC%E7%AB%8B%E6%80%A7\"><span class=\"toc-text\">事件的独立性</span></a></li></ol>","author":{"name":"C4IN","slug":"blog-author","avatar":"/pic/au.jpg","link":"/","description":"","socials":{"github":"","twitter":"","stackoverflow":"","wechat":"","qq":"","weibo":"","zhihu":"","csdn":"","juejin":"","customs":{}}},"mapped":true,"hidden":false,"prev_post":{"title":"随机变量的分布","uid":"b3e44aa0e168a95d6665895a968d23a2","slug":"随机变量的分布","date":"2023-09-14T02:14:41.000Z","updated":"2023-09-17T10:29:13.877Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/随机变量的分布.json","keywords":null,"cover":[],"text":"随机变量及分布函数变量的特点： 变量的取值由随机试验的结果来确定; 取各数值的可能性大小有确定的统计规律性. 上述变量称为随机变量,它可以完整地描述试验结果，从...","permalink":"/post/随机变量的分布","photos":[],"count_time":{"symbolsCount":"2.6k","symbolsTime":"2 mins."},"categories":[{"name":"概率论与数理统计","slug":"概率论与数理统计","count":4,"path":"api/categories/概率论与数理统计.json"}],"tags":[],"author":{"name":"C4IN","slug":"blog-author","avatar":"/pic/au.jpg","link":"/","description":"","socials":{"github":"","twitter":"","stackoverflow":"","wechat":"","qq":"","weibo":"","zhihu":"","csdn":"","juejin":"","customs":{}}},"feature":true},"next_post":{"title":"Java类和对象","uid":"e8805eec5bdd2acbc81f5c8e275b0c0a","slug":"Java类和对象","date":"2023-09-05T06:23:22.000Z","updated":"2023-09-17T11:28:30.204Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/Java类和对象.json","keywords":null,"cover":[],"text":"Java类和对象类的变量描述对象的属性，类的方法体现对象的行为。封装在类中的这些数据的变量和方法，为对象的创建提供了模板。对象之间的交互作用